  "prompt": "Which is the best camera phone performance under 10000?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, finding a smartphone with the **best camera performance under \u20b910,000** in India can be challenging due to budget constraints. However, some phones offer decent camera capabilities in this price range. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n---\n\n### **Best Camera Phones Under \u20b910,000**\n\n1. **Redmi 12C**\n   - **Primary Camera**: 50 MP (main) + depth sensor\n   - **Selfie Camera**: 5 MP\n   - **Features**: AI scene detection, portrait mode, and night mode\n   - **Performance**: Budget-friendly with decent camera performance for the price.\n\n2. **realme Narzo N55**\n   - **Primary Camera**: 64 MP (main) + 2 MP depth\n   - **Selfie Camera**: 8 MP\n   - **Features**: Super nightscape, AI scene enhancement, and street photography mode\n   - **Performance**: Good for daylight photography with decent low-light capabilities.\n\n3. **Samsung Galaxy M04**\n   - **Primary Camera**: 13 MP (main) + 2 MP depth\n   - **Selfie Camera**: 5 MP\n   - **Features**: Portrait mode and basic AI enhancements\n   - **Performance**: Reliable camera for casual photography.\n\n4. **Infinix Smart 7 HD**\n   - **Primary Camera**: 13 MP (main) + AI lens\n   - **Selfie Camera**: 5 MP\n   - **Features**: AI beauty mode and bokeh effect\n   - **Performance**: Entry-level camera performance, suitable for basic usage.\n\n---\n\n### **What to Expect**\n- **Daylight Photos**: Most phones in this range will produce decent results in good lighting.\n- **Low-Light Photos**: Quality may suffer due to limited hardware and software enhancements.\n- **Video Recording**: Expect 1080p video recording with basic stabilization.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Tips**\n- Prioritize phones with higher megapixel counts (e.g., 50 MP or 64 MP) for better detail.\n- Look for dedicated camera modes like night mode, portrait mode, and HDR for enhanced results.\n- Consider older models or discounted phones from previous generations for better value.\n\n---\n\nIf you can stretch your budget slightly (\u20b912,000\u2013\u20b915,000), you\u2019ll find significantly better camera performance in phones like the Redmi Note 12 or realme Narzo 60x.",
